Title: Down Payment
Description: Track down the workers who betrayed Giacomo
ObjectiveProposalResponse: A place of rest for weary travelers, of course! I am Giacomo Altoviti, architect. Perhaps you have heard of me? No? \n\nWell, you would have if my workmen hadn't stabbed me in the back - literally - and run off with my design notebook and tools.
InProgressResponse: Your aid is welcome, friend. Once we have my notebook, I have such plans. It will change all of Aeternum! \nAnd you will be greatly rewarded, fear not!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Is that my notebook? Oh, grazie! \n\nAnd what of those bastardi who stabbed me and stole it? The one who had it was Corrupted! Hah! A fitting end to his greed and treachery!

Title: A Major Purchase
Description: Purchase a home, and place some decorations within
ObjectiveProposalResponse:
It is sanctuary! A haven that beckons after a long day. It anchors you to the land. 

And spirit shrines can deposit you gently inside from anywhere on the island! 

To truly understand, you must purchase a home of your own.
InProgressResponse: Raising the capital for your first home may not be easy, but I promise you, the benefits are worthwhile.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Good friend, you have returned! And looking stronger and more prosperous than before. \n\nYou have made your purchase, yes?

Title: Insuring the Investment
Description: Travel to Shatterwall and the Fong Family Orchard to collect fresh Withered blood and bones for Giacomo
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Eh, of a sort. I have selected the site to prepare the foundation, but I'll need a few things. \n\nAn associate in First Light gave me a recipe to work the blood and bones of those Withered... things... into the mortar.
InProgressResponse: To be honest, I'm not entirely certain how the bones and blood will work, but my Survivalist friend swears by it. I figured better safe than sorry, no?
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Welcome to the site of the first Traveler's Rest! It may not seem much right now, but I promise you... it will be! \nNow, have you gathered those grisly bits I needed?

Title: Insuring the Investment (Part 2)
Description: Gather Grave Nettles from Nettlerest Graveyard, and bring them back to Giacomo
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Si, a plant that grows on and around gravesites. Some people still go through the ceremony for those who have become Lost.  \nThere is a graveyard east of here that should have what we need.
InProgressResponse: Scuse, I do not mean to impose on you, but I am certain that when you see the result, you will be amazed.
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: See my accomplishment? Amazing progress, no? The foundation is almost finished. I even had time to add storage for supplies! \n\nDid you recover the Grave Nettles?

Title: Site Inspection
Description: Gather the construction materials for Giacomo, and investigate the information on the next traitor
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Si, si! I'm also running short of materials. I had planned this project with a work crew behind me, but we saw how that turned out. Well, until it is completed, someone must remain here to defend the site. \n\nI have a list of what I need, if you're willing?
InProgressResponse: I've almost exhausted my stockpile. \n\nBut I have confidence you'll handle matters swiftly, and return with good news and packs of supplies!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Magnifico! Now, travelers have a haven from the dangers and horrors of this island. \n\n This is my dream: a home for all who need it.

Title: Mandatory Improvements
Description: Collect the materials for Giacomo's recipe, then craft the Ancient Protection Stones at an Arcane Repository
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Listen carefully - I've rediscovered how the Ancients protected some of their sites. Ah! Ah! \n\nThis secret could better safeguard the Traveler's Rest! It could change the future of Aeternum!
InProgressResponse: Because I am cautious, there are a few steps not in that recipe that I'll keep secretâ€¦ at least for now. But in time, I'll share my knowledge. But not for a profit!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse: Bentornato! And just in time! This road is well-traveled. I've had my hands full keeping the less friendly sorts away. \n\nWere you able to create the stones as I asked?

Title: Closing Cost
Description: Track down Airic Niclisson, the leader of those who betrayed Giacomo
ObjectiveProposalResponse: Si, Airic Niclisson, the foreman of my treacherous crew. I'm certain he was the mastermind of their scheme. \n\nThe trouble is, I've received no word of him, which means the scoundrel is hiding.
InProgressResponse: Just preparing for the road, then I'm on my way. I hope to find Airic myself. But I'm uncertain what to do then. \n\nAt least find out what happened to the rest of my tools... beyond that, who knows? Good luck to you, friend!
DestinationCompletionAvailableResponse:
Friend! Any news? 

You found him! What did that scoundrel say when faceded with his crimes? 

E fatta. He got what he deserved.
